{
  "stem": "15686.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then we arrived in New York in October of 1941.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Did you speak English?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I spoke a little bit of English, because I had-- both in Germany, and in France in school, we were required to take a foreign language.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in Germany, having no idea that I would someday go to France, I had opted for English, because we were going to the United States, you know, quote, unquote.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And I had studied some English.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And little did I know that I would have to learn French.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in New York, when apparently the story of this voyage, which-- which was the last trip that the ship made before the US entered into the war-- the story of this little odyssey had made the news papers, or the news media in New York.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were met outside of New York Harbor by a-- I guess it was a Coast Guard cutter or something full of news people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had film cameras.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In those days, they had the movietone news, or whatever they call that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was a newsreel-- newsreel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there were some reporters that came on board, and they rounded up this bunch of kids, who had been ignored throughout the voyage by all the other passengers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, we were the very important people that the press came to meet.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And And they rounded us up, and they took pictures of us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they wanted to know if somebody spoke English.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I said, well, I speak very little.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they said, OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was the oldest, so they started to say, well, you know, are you OK?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Are you happy to be here?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
